<HEAD>Thunderstorms Sweep Through Much Of The Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms swept across sections of the Midwest, South and
Northeast today after causing damage in sections of Minnesota and
Wisconsin.
   An intense line of thunderstorms that developed ahead of a cold
front spawned high winds that blew down trees and power lines in
southeast Minnesota and western Wisconsin on Sunday evening. The
thunderstorms weakened overnight and drifted into central Wisconsin
and northern Iowa.
   Other thunderstorms rumbled across northern Georgia, southern
Alabama, Louisiana and Mississippi early today.
   Rain and thunderstorms were scattered across eastern Nebraska,
western Kansas, Vermont, New Hampshire and the Carolinas.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms scattered
from Florida across southeast Louisiana; and from upper Michigan
into central Colorado.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 70s to 80s over the
northern Atlantic Coast states, Pennsylvania, the Great Lakes
region, upper Mississippi Valley, Northern Plains, upper Missouri
Valley, the Northwest and along the California coast; near 100 over
much of Oklahoma and the eastern Texas; between near 100 and 110
over the Desert Southwest; and 90s across most of the rest of the
nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 45
degrees at Kalispell, Mont., to 93 at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 70 fair; Boston 77 cloudy; Buffalo 66 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 72 fair; Cincinnati 64 fair; Cleveland 67 fair;
Detroit 71 fair; Miami 77 fair; New York 77 fair; Philadelphia 76
fair; Pittsburgh 63 fair; Portland 69 cloudy; Washington 74 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 57 cloudy; Chicago 77 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
86 fair; Denver 62 partly cloudy; Des Moines 84 partly cloudy;
Indianapolis 68 fair; Kansas City 85 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 72
cloudy; Nashville 78 fair; New Orleans 77 foggy; St. Louis 82 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 71 partly cloudy; Anchorage 56 partly cloudy;
Las Vegas 77 fair; Los Angeles 64 fair; Phoenix 90 fair; Salt Lake
City 57 fair; San Diego 67 cloudy; San Francisco 57 fair; Seattle
57 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 68 fair; Toronto 61 fair.
