<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--China-Storm     08-08 0134</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--China-Storm,0141</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>49 Confirmed Dead In Shanxi Storm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A weekend rainstorm that inundated parts of
northern China killed 49 people and left 10 others missing, a
newspaper said Monday.
   The People's Daily reported that Saturday's storm also left
30,000 peasants without homes.
   It said rain fell on Fenyang county in Shanxi province for more
than three hours Saturday.
   Several counties in Shanxi were evacuated after the Yellow River
Friday rose to flood levels in several places for the first time
this year, the report said.
   More than 800 people have died in floods this year in China.
   Also Monday, winds of up to 75 mph uprooted hundreds of trees in
the eastern city of Hangzhou, felling water and electricity lines,
according to the weather station in the province of Zhejiang.
</TEXT>
