<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Americans believe the United States has moved
toward racial equality during the past quarter century, but a
majority say society remains racist overall, a Media
General-Associated Press poll has found.
   Twenty-five years after the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. declared
his dream of equal opportunity, more than eight in 10 respondents
in the poll said the goal is closer and seven in 10 said it is
attainable.
   But while 54 percent said blacks and other minorities have the
same opportunities as whites in the United States, a sizable 42
percent of all respondents, including 69 percent of blacks,
disagreed.
</TEXT>
