<HEAD>Space Telescope Running Up Big Bills Waiting For Delayed Launch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SUNNYVALE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Edwin P. Hubble Space Telescope is
to float next year from a space shuttle beyond the haze of
atmosphere to let scientists peer into the depths of the universe
and 14 billion years into the past.
   It should see seven times as far as the most powerful
