<1ST_LINE>r f BC-WeeklySteel     08-08 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Fell 3.8 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production fell to 1.890 million tons in
the week ended Aug. 6, a decrease of 3.8 percent from the previous
week's 1.965 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 88.6 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 92.1 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
60.437 million net tons, an increase of 20.1 percent from the
50.324 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 90.1 percent of capacity,
compared with 75.1 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Aug. 6: Northeast
Coast, 270,000; Pittsburgh, 194,000; Youngstown, 85,000; Lake Erie,
157,000; Detroit, 150,000; Chicago, 521,000; Midwest, 200,000;
Southern, 217,000; and Western, 96,000.
</TEXT>
